# Clearing Stored SDD Match Data

## Related Queries

- "delete SDD matches"
- "clear sensitive data from SA_FSDLP_MatchHits"
- "remove stored match data Access Analyzer"
- "SDD matches still showing after scan"

## Overview

This article explains how to clear stored SDD match data from the database.

This approach removes the sensitive data captured in match results but keeps the scan results themselves, such as match counts and criteria.

To prevent new match data from being stored, disable SDD match storage in the SEEK System Scan configuration before clearing existing data.

If the goal is to remove SDD matches entirely, use the `FS_SDD_DELETE` instant job instead:
- **NAA v12.0:** [InstantJobs\FS_SDD_DELETE](https://docs.netwrix.com/docs/accessanalyzer/12_0/admin/jobs/instantjobs/fs_sdd_delete)
- **NAA v11.6:** [InstantJobs\FS_SDD_DELETE](https://docs.netwrix.com/docs/accessanalyzer/11_6/admin/jobs/instantjobs/fs_sdd_delete)

## Instructions

1. Open the **SEEK System Scan** query configuration.
2. On the _Sensitive Data Settings_ tab, uncheck the option **Store discovered sensitive data**.
> This will prevent the sensitive data from being stored on the next collection.
> 
![Disabling SDD match storage in SEEK System Scan configuration](./../0-images/fsaa-store-discovered-sdd.webp)

1. In the Netwrix Access Analyzer SQL database, run the following SQL statement:

```sql
UPDATE SA_FSDLP_MatchHits
SET MatchData = NULL,
    MatchPrefix = NULL,
    MatchSuffix = NULL
```
> This will clear out all previously stored match hits.